40|$|A cross {{correlation}} analysis of coronal green line intensity (5303 A) and interplanetary magnetic field polarity {{for the period}} 1947 - 1970 shows that the coronal features are organized in a constant pattern {{with respect to the}} 4 -sector structure through the solar cycle. A sudden inversion of the coronal pattern with respect to the sector structure takes place at the <b>solar</b> <b>minima.</b> The high emission regions of the green corona are located near the solar magnetic sector boundaries having polarities (-,+), (+,-), (-,+) during cycles 18, 19, 20 respectively in the Northern Hemisphere, and (+,-), (-,+), (+,-) in the Southern Hemisphere...|$|R
